mScripts.name: General service
mScripts.description: Contains the steps necessary for recording and publishing a standard service where the reading and the sermon follow each other without a song separating them.

mSteps.description: Please enter the required information about the service and then select 'Mark as completed'. Data entered here will appear on the content web page, the RSS/podcast title and the MP3 file name and tags.

mLeftInputLevelProperty.description: Displays the current left input level as a value between 0 and 100. Displays the current right input level as a value between 0 and 100. If the dBFS scale is used, the 100 represents 0dBFS and 0 represents -50dBFS. Otherwise it represents the (scaled) raw readings.

mUseDbProperty.description: Specifies whether the meters should show the signal readings in dBFS (logarithmic) or raw (linear). For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mHeadroomProperty.description: Specifies the headroom in dBFS. This must be a number between 0 and 18. For an explanation of the headroom please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headroom. For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mSteps.name: Record pre-sermon
mSteps.description: Records the first part of the service before the reading and sermon begins. This part will not be published but be burned to CD. It records from the main audio input line to an uncompressed WAV file. Please make sure that the input level will not exceed the maximum.

mUseDbProperty.description: Specifies whether the meters should show the signal readings in dBFS (logarithmic) or raw (linear). For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mHeadroomProperty.description: Specifies the headroom in dBFS. This must be a number between 0 and 18. For an explanation of the headroom please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headroom. For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mSteps.name: Record sermon
mSteps.description: Records the sermon (and the reading). It records from the main audio input line to an uncompressed WAV file. Please make sure that the input level will not exceed the maximum.

mUseDbProperty.description: Specifies whether the meters should show the signal readings in dBFS (logarithmic) or raw (linear). For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mHeadroomProperty.description: Specifies the headroom in dBFS. This must be a number between 0 and 18. For an explanation of the headroom please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headroom. For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mSteps.name: Record post-sermon
mSteps.description: Records the part of the service after the sermon. It records from the main audio input line to an uncompressed WAV file. Please make sure that the input level will not exceed the maximum.

mUseDbProperty.description: Specifies whether the meters should show the signal readings in dBFS (logarithmic) or raw (linear). For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mHeadroomProperty.description: Specifies the headroom in dBFS. This must be a number between 0 and 18. For an explanation of the headroom please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headroom. For an explanation of dBFS, please refer to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS.

mSteps.name: Convert sermon recording to MP3
mSteps.description: Converts the sermon recording from WAVE to MP3 format using the LAME encoder. Note: This converter uses average bit rate (ABR) encoding and not CBR or VBR.

mMp3FolderReferenceParameter.description: Specifies a reference to the folder where the new MP3 entry should be stored.

mMp3EntryReferenceResult.description: Contains a reference to the MP3 entry that has been converted.

mSteps.name: Publish sermon as MP3
mSteps.description: Publishes a new MP3 recording to the CCB web site and creates/updates the podcast RSS file accordingly. In order to achieve this, first uploads the MP3 file and than it generates the content web page from the content page header and footer locally. It does the same for the podcast file and then uploads both files replacing the older versions.

mMp3Folders.name: Sermon MP3 recordings
mMp3Folders.description: Contains the sermon MP3 recordings whether not yet published, published or archived.

mSteps.name: Republish MP3s
mSteps.description: Updates the sermon MP3 recordings on the web site and creates/updates the podcast RSS file accordingly. In order to achieve this, it first uploads the MP3 files that are not yet published (and already published ones, depending on the 'Republish MP3 files' parameter) and then it generates the content web page from the content page header and footer locally. It does the same for the podcast file and then uploads both files replacing the older versions. It reads the states of the MP3 entries to determine whether to publish or unpublish.
